    dc:title "Taxonomic monograph of Eugenia sect. Schizocalomyrtus (Myrtaceae: Myrteae), a group within Eugenia with unusual flowers" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649290> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5649290>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Diversity of Eugenia sect. Schizocalomyrtus. A–B. Eugenia acutata. A. Auxotelic inflorescence undergoing a second phase of vegetative growth. B. Flowers at anthesis. C–D. Eugenia tenuipedunculata. C. Flowers. D. Immature fruits. E. Eugenia neoriedeliana. Flower opening via transversal tearing at the calyx base resulting in a calyptra-like structure. F. Eugenia guanabarina. Flowers opening via transversal tearing at the calyx base resulting in a calyptra-like structure (S) placed in opposition to a petal (P). G–H. Eugenia longohypanthiata. G. Flower bud tearing irregularly at anthesis. H. Immature fruits crowned by the remnant of the calyx lobes (S) and the hypanthium (H). (A–B: A. Giaretta 1460; C: J.E.Q. Faria 1000; D: A. Giaretta 1493; E: A. Giaretta 1489; F: A. Giaretta 1035; G: A. Giaretta 1500; H: A. Giaretta 1502). Photos by A. Giaretta, except C by J.E.Q. Faria." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5649290/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

